My friends, I too am a poor university student with a laptop.  Two weeks ago,
a guy came to my OS/2 user's group meeting and introduced me to what has
become a RELIGIOUS experience.  DCF/2 is an on-the-fly data compression
utility for OS/2 that has NON of the drawbacks DOS compression utilities have.
It is 32-bit, integrated with th OS/2 kernel, multithreaded, and fast.  Try
it for free!  on hobbes it is in /os2/new and /demos as trydcf4d.zip.  It is
also on other OS/2 sites.  hobbes=hobbes.nmsu.edu.  They also have a web page
at http://www.primenet.com/~grock/dcf2.html .  I am not related to the company
other than as a VERY satisfied customer.  I have 1 gig on my laptop HD ;-)

