After reading this post I decided that it might serve some good if people had
some more accounts of DCF/2.

I purchased DCF/2 v1.4 in may and received Partition Magic free.  All for just $100.
Partition Magic itself is an amazing product with OS/2 and DOS text-mode versions
and an OS/2 PM GUI version all in the same package.  Great manual too.

DCF/2 v1.4 has fully restored my confidence in on -the-fly compression.  It has
many safety features and automatic functions that make my life easier.  I'm so
confident with it that I've compressed all my OS/2 and WIndows games, Windows
apps, multimedia files and documentation/INF files.  All together I've saved
50MB of space.  And I'm not done yet.
Getting info on the drive is very simple, as if running optimization utilities.
It is integrated with the OS/2 system very well.
Compression levels and priorities are all adjustable for your preferred level of
performance.   Although I didn't take Max up on the idea of reset my system to
test DCF/2's reliability, I did have to reset my system this week.  Sure enough,
all 128MB of data on the compressed drive were completely intact.
At the moment I'm running at 1.8:1 compression ratio.

I knew this product was worth $100 with PMagic, but you can't go wrong for $30!!!!
$30 won't even buy some of today's shareware.  If you need even a few extra
MB of space, or are unimpressed by the size of the bonuspak, get this product now!

The usual disclaimers apply about not being affiliated in any way with proportional
software.

Check hobbes or walnut creek for the v1.4 demo ZIP file.  It allows you to test all
the features and compression.

